  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (c247243 2022-07-15T00:04:58.638841575Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil -f\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI'm trying to use Anvil to fork BNB Chain mainnet.\r\nThe following code succeeds in hardhat, but fails in anvil (it seems as if the storage slot is not set). I also tried changing `hardhat_setStorageAt` to `anvil_setStorageAt` but it gives the same result\r\n\r\n```\r\nfrom web3 import Web3\r\nimport eth_abi\r\nimport requests\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nbusd_address = \"0xe9e7CEA3DedcA5984780Bafc599bD69ADd087D56\"\r\n\r\nhardhat_url = \"http://localhost:8545\"\r\n\r\n\r\nw3 = Web3(Web3.HTTPProvider(\"http://localhost:8545\"))\r\nbusd_abi = json.load(open(\"interfaces/BUSD.json\"))\r\nbusd_contract = w3.eth.contract(address=busd_address, abi=busd_abi)\r\n\r\ndef set_busd_balance(address, balance):\r\n    account = Web3.toChecksumAddress(address)\r\n    slot = 1\r\n    abi_encoded = eth_abi.encode_abi(['address', 'uint256'], [account, slot])\r\n    map_slot = Web3.solidityKeccak([\"bytes\"], [\"0x\" + abi_encoded.hex()]).hex()\r\n\r\n    value = Web3.toHex(balance)\r\n    while len(value) < 64+2:\r\n        value = \"0x0\" + value[2:]\r\n    set_storage_request = {\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"hardhat_setStorageAt\", \"id\": 1,\r\n        \"params\": [busd_address, map_slot, value]}\r\n    requests.post(hardhat_url, json.dumps(set_storage_request)).json()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef test_busd_balance_slot():\r\n    account = \"0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\"\r\n    set_busd_balance(account, 12345)\r\n\r\n    balance = busd_contract.caller().balanceOf(account)\r\n    assert balance == 12345\r\n\r\n\r\ntest_busd_balance_slot()\r\n```",
